    "description": "Okaya Electric Industries Co., Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, engages in the manufacture and sale of electrical components and equipment in Japan and internationally. The company offers noise suppression products, such as noise suppression capacitors, spark killers, high pulse capacitors, noise filters, and common mode choke coils; surge protective devices (SPD), including module, PCB mounted, and SMD type SPD; LED display devices and lighting source products; and sensor products. Its products are used in air conditioner, refrigerators, cooking appliances, audiovisual and communication equipment, medical equipment, industrial equipment, and urban infrastructure. The company was formerly known as Okaya Radio Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Okaya Electric Industries Co., Ltd. in 1967. Okaya Electric Industries Co., Ltd. was incorporated in 1939 and is headquartered in Setagaya, Japan."
